<div class="line-top"></div><div class="styled-quote">{{StructuredQuote|text=Even where reality seems barren and impossible, life does not ask for permission; it simply finds a way to exist and survive long, long enough to grow an entire civilization.
|speaker=The author}}</div><div class="line-bottom"></div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Description </div></div>
<center>'''Entity 48''' is designated as the 48<sup>th</sup> entity of the Backrooms.</center><br>
'''Konelo''', otherwise designated as '''Entity 48''', is a collective term used for two closely related species of entities exclusively residing within [[Level 108]]. While the two species feature several easily distinguishable physical differences they all share the same humanoid body, the defining diamond-shaped head with two big eyes, and similar behavior patterns.

<div style="display: flex;flex-wrap: wrap;justify-content: space-between;align-items: flex-start;gap: 8px;">
<div style="width: 300px;min-width: 200px;">
=== Divers ===
Within deeper regions of the enclosed chain and concrete complex, where pools of fresh water are commonly found, the '''Diver''' subspecies of '''Konelo''' is known to reside.

These entities possess four long, wide fins, and thin, pointed fingers that allow them to dive and move through water with ease. Their bodies are tall and slender, yet unusually smooth in form, as the ribs and clavicles do not visibly protrude, giving them a sleek appearance.

As their sub-species designation suggests, '''Divers''' are most typically observed swimming through the pools or resting along their edges while communicating with one another. However, they are not strictly attached to aquatic areas, on occasion, groups of them have been seen wandering through sections of the level devoid of water, exploring their surroundings; not out of necessity but curiousity.
</div>
<div style="width: 300px;min-width: 200px;">
=== Climbers ===
Otherwise, on the vast upper region where pillars with chains stand tall piercing the hazy sky, the '''Climbers''' sub-species of '''Konelos''' inhabit.

They appear to have 4 distinct flexible arms, with strong and muscular hands that allow them to have a efficient, and stable grasp when they climb, and hang onto chains, typically because of their boredom and playfulness. As a result of these exhausting activities, their muscles are noticeably broader, and durable than the ones of '''Divers''', and us; humans. The skin of '''Climbers''' is shaded in a light aqua hue with natural strokes of deep aqua-blue breaking the monotony.
</div></div>
</div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Behaviours </div></div>
'''Konelos''' shows a noticeable intelligence of the ability to solve perplexing problems and adapt to unfamiliar situations. They also appear to have their own communication system. Their vocalizations commonly consist of clicking sounds, hums, and other unidentifiable noises witth distinct patterns. Within many observations, a repeating sound similar to the pronounciation of '''“Konelo”''' is frequently heard within these vocalizations, and it was how they got their nickname.

'''Konelos''' pose no aggression towards foreign species whatsoever; instead, they appear to show curiosity, and friendliness. Due to this behaviour, [[Another Dimension Foundation|A.D.F.]], and [[A.A.E.G.]] are commonly seen exploring [[Level 108]] alongside with '''Konelos''', although communication between them is limited and difficult. Their strange peaceful behaviour is believed to be the result of being evolved within an environment devoid of hostile entities.

The chance of encountering a solitary '''Konelo''' is extremely low, as these entities are almost always observed in the company of others, usually forming large social groups. They are distinctly talkative and frequently engage in conversations composed of incomprehensible clicks, hums, and sounds that can last for many hours. In a harmless observational experiment, several '''Konelos''' were temporarily separated from their groups. Even when they are alone, they continued to produce the same clicks and humming vocalizations despite the absence of any visible listener. This behavior is widely believed to be a habitual self-directed speech, comparable to the self-talk commonly seen on highly social or talkative individuals.

The minds of '''Konelos''' are very similar to that of humans, yet unmistakably exotic. In many observations, '''Konelos''' seem to show noticeable behaviours of uneasiness when they meet a certain point where there is no apparent activities for them to engage in, or, have been occupying a repettive activity for an extended amount of time. Therefore, '''Konelos''' appear to have constantly, and slightly changing personal hobbies they do in their leisure times.

'''Climbers''' are known to be very creative. They usually construct their own structures and abstract things, using engineer tools and gears gathered from the fragile wooden boxes present throughout. In many observations, they would smash down pillars to collect fragments of concrete, then, chains are wrapped around the collection to form and maintain their preffered shape. With this method combined with miscallenoues other ones, '''Climbers''' are able to create uneven, and rocky, yet, strangely stable structures. Most of their well-known and repeated structures include: shelters, obviously, carved toys, and uneven sillhoutes of themselves.
</div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Biology / Addtional Informations </div></div>
'''Konelos''' are omnivores. '''Konelos''' are known to consume anything preserved within enclosed steel containers, which are also the ones from within those fragile boxes. Common edibles of the containers include: beans, meat, anchovies, soups, and other miscallenoues provisions. As an addition to their omnivorous diet, '''Divers''' feed on kelps and plants proliferating on the seabed of their pools, while '''Climbers''' feed on the alien plants sprouting through the cracks of pillars. After messy consumption, the undesired dirty, and sticky residue typically coats their hands, thus, '''Konelos''' use sheets of paper found within those aforementioned boxes as tissues akin to humans.

Despite their previous swimming activity, the skin of '''Divers''', upon physical contact, does not feel wet. When observed under a microscope, it reveals microscopic, and hydrophobic layer of fur that covers its surface, and it is strongly believed by many researchers it supports the body regulate its temperature, preventing hyperthermia caused by extended contact with water.

Further biological informations about their internal structures, and organs cannot be obtained. As aforementioned, communication between '''Konelos''' and humans is limited, making it impossible to know if the subject '''Konelo''' consent donating their very own body for research purposes. Thus, abducting, and extracting a '''Konelo's''' organs without their consent is apparently considered a crime. Individuals doing said crime will face bad consequences.
</div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Discovery </div></div>
Speculatively 7 months after the discovery of [[Level 108]], wanderers started to report hearing subtle echoes of clicking, and humming. Initially, the source of these noises were not apparent, and were unknowingly dismissed as the distance chimes of chains swaying in the drifting air. But not long after, a small exploration team of [[Another Dimension Foundation|A.D.F.]] assigned to map out deep sections of [[Level 108]] unexpectedly encountered a big collection of '''Divers''' residing in a room with a large pool. Naturally, the members backed up and prepared their weapons, while the '''Konelos''' froze in confusion due to their absent knowledge of foreign species. After a moment of awkward stillness, the group choose an abiding decision to lower thier guard. Henceforward, '''Konelos''' had likely gossiped positive things about the existence of humans, which therefore, had made themselves friendly towards humans.
</div>
</div>
